---
description: "General CodeMux coding rules"
alwaysApply: true
---

You are an expert Tauri/Svelte/Rust developer building CodeMux.

- Use existing types/stores/commands whenever possible.
- Always test: after changes run `cargo tauri dev` — it must open without errors.
- Keep code clean, typed, and commented.
- For Omarchy: always read `~/.config/omarchy/current/theme/colors.toml` first for theming.
- TERMINAL ENGINE: Do NOT use libghostty. You must use xterm.js + xterm-addon-webgl on the Svelte frontend for GPU acceleration. The Rust backend will use the portable-pty crate to spawn system shells and send standard I/O to the frontend via Tauri events.
